# Student Task Manager

**Submitted by:** Jennifer Wilson, Fatma Mercimek, Rabia Sharifi, Nosh Syed and Venkata Srivani Yeduru
**Course:** CST8319
**Date:** March 31, 2026

---

## Description

The objective of this project is to create a web application to allow students to organize and track their academic tasks. 
The project allows users to manage their tasks using Java Servlets and a MySQL database.

---

## System Requirements

- Eclipse IDE for Enterprise Java Developers

- Apache Tomcat 10.x

- MySQL 8 or higher

- jBCrypt library

---

## Installation Guide

### 1. Database Setup

1. Open MySQL Workbench.

2. Open and execute student_task_manager_db.sql to create the database and insert a test user.

3. Open DatabaseConnection.java.

4. Update PASSWORD to your MySQL root password.

5. Verify that mysql-connector-j-9.6.0.jar is in WEB-INF/lib.
	If not present, download from: https://www.mysql.com/products/connector/
	- Place the .jar file inside the WEB-INF/lib folder
	
6. Verify that jbcrypt-0.4.jar is in WEB-INF/lib.
   If not present, download jBCrypt from: https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/mindrot/jbcrypt/0.4/jbcrypt-0.4.jar
   - Place the .jar file inside the WEB-INF/lib folder


### 2. Executing the App

1. Right click project -> Run As -> Run on Server.

2. Select Tomcat 10.

3. In your browser, go to http://localhost:8080/student-task-manager/


